# =============================================================================
# DAY 1 dialog strings
# =============================================================================
d1_l01: .asciiz "The bells of the Lower Sanctum toll five times. You wake\nin a bed too large for one man, in a hall too cold for the\nliving. Today you sit the throne for the first time.\nToday you are king.\n"
d1_l02: .asciiz "My lord. Your eyes are open, the realm holds its breath.\nI am your Advisor. The Priesthood raised you for this hour.\nListen well, and the four realms will listen to you.\n"
d1_l03: .asciiz "Four powers share this underground kingdom. Vampires, who\nguard the gates. Miners, who feed us all. Priests, my own\norder, who keep the old promise. And the Lithari - the ones\nwho used to be miners until the Crystal took them. Today\nthey will all stand before you.\n"
d1_l04: .asciiz "Watch their bars. Each realm has four numbers: a special\nstat, aggression, strength, and influence. Keep them in\nmind. A kingdom is balance.\n"
d1_l05: .asciiz "Edmure of the Night Guard. We have held your borders since\nthe Fool King's day. We do not ask for thanks. We ask only\nwhat was promised: blood enough to keep our soldiers\nstanding.\n"
d1_l06: .asciiz "(whisper) The vampires have a Hunger stat. Let it climb\ntoo high and they will take what is not given.\n"
d1_l07: .asciiz "Grimor, foreman of the deep shafts. My people dig until our\nhands break. We ask only that we are not bled dry while we\ndo it. Speak fair to us and the picks keep swinging.\n"
d1_l08: .asciiz "(whisper) The miners feed the kingdom. If their Strength\nfalls, no realm eats.\n"
d1_l09: .asciiz "Father Thomas, of the Order. I knew your mother, my lord.\nI knew the hands that wrote your name in the book. The\nGreat Deliverance is near, and you are the one chosen to\nsee it done. Trust me as she trusted me.\n"
d1_l10: .asciiz "(whisper) The Priesthood is the oldest power. Their\nInfluence over the crown is already high. Be careful what\nyou owe them.\n"
d1_l11: .asciiz "Valar, of the Crystal Choir. We do not ask, we do not beg.\nWe only remind: every soul that turns to crystal is one we\nwill not return. The deep is awake. So is its mother.\n"
d1_l12: .asciiz "(whisper) The Lithari rarely speak. When they do, listen\ntwice.\n"
d1_l13: .asciiz "That is the Court, my lord. The first day is done. Rest.\nThe night underground is long, and the dreams here are\nnot always your own.\n"

d1_n01: .asciiz "The walls of your chamber dissolve. The floor becomes a\nmirror of pale violet crystal. Shafts of ice-blue light\nfall from nowhere. A figure stands at the far end,\nwoman-shaped, made of the light itself.\n"
d1_n02: .asciiz "At last. In all this noise, I can finally speak to you\nface to face.\n"
d1_n03: .asciiz "I know the weight on your shoulders. The mask they want\nyou to wear. The savior they made of you before you were\nold enough to refuse.\n"
d1_n04: .asciiz "(thinking) Who are you? How did you enter my mind?\n"
d1_n05: .asciiz "I am only the one who listens to the echoes. And yours\necho loud. Tomorrow many voices will ask you for a piece\nof yourself. Every smile hides an expectation. Every\nanger hides a fear.\n"
d1_n06: .asciiz "(thinking) Why are you telling me this? I already know\nmy path.\n"
d1_n07: .asciiz "I am asking you to see with your own eyes. There is no\npure good and no pure evil here. Only choices, and the\nprice they carry. Do not trust the loudest truth. Trust\nthe quiet voice inside. When the time comes - trust me.\n"
d1_n08: .asciiz "The light spins around her. The dream collapses. You wake\nin your own bed, sweating, the taste of crystal dust on\nyour tongue.\n"

# =============================================================================
# DAY 2 dialog strings - The Turning Child
# =============================================================================
d2_l01: .asciiz "A miner family was caught hiding their daughter. The child\nis turning. Crystal grows on her arm. The Priesthood demands\nshe be handed to them. The Lithari demand she be sent to\nthe deep. They wait on your word, my lord.\n"
d2_l02: .asciiz "There is no return from the Turn, my lord. The child is no\nlonger a child. She is a seed of the Crystal, and the\nCrystal does not stop. Give her to the Order. We will see\nto it that no other home burns.\n"
d2_l03: .asciiz "She is one of ours now. We did not call her. The Crystal\ndid. We will keep her safe in the deep, where she can grow\nwithout harming the surface. This is mercy. Theirs is a knife.\n"
d2_l04: .asciiz "(quietly) She is six years old, my king. Whatever you\ndecide, decide it remembering that.\n"

d2_choice1_q: .asciiz "\n>>> What is your judgement?\n"
d2_choice1_a: .asciiz "  A) Hand the child to the Priesthood.\n"
d2_choice1_b: .asciiz "  B) Send the child to the Lithari.\n"

d2_after_a:   .asciiz "A wise ruling, my lord. The Order will not forget where\nyou stood on this day.\n"
d2_after_b:   .asciiz "The deep will remember this. So will I.\n"

d2_n_a:       .asciiz "From the high window of your chamber you watch a cart\nroll out of the castle gate. Sacks bounce in the back.\nFrom one sack, a single shard of pale crystal falls onto\nthe road. A child's scream cuts through the night - then\nnothing.\n"
d2_n_b:       .asciiz "You see? She is laughing. The deep is gentle with the\nsmall ones. You chose well. I will not forget either.\n"

# =============================================================================
# DAY 3 dialog strings - The Blood Tax
# =============================================================================
d3_l01: .asciiz "The vampires come for their blood ration today. There is\nsickness in the lower shafts. Edmure will ask for more than\nthe agreed share. Grimor will refuse him. Be ready.\n"
d3_l02: .asciiz "Old agreements are old for a reason. The Fool King swore\nus blood in exchange for the sword. We have kept the sword\nsharp for three hundred years. Now the ration is short,\nand my soldiers are weak. Take it from the healthy ones.\nThey can spare it.\n"
d3_l03: .asciiz "The healthy ones are dying too, leech. The plague does not\ncheck their papers. Take their blood and you take the picks,\nthe bread, the whole kingdom under your boots. I will not\ngive it.\n"
d3_l04_rahip: .asciiz "My king - the Order stands with you, whatever you decide.\nThe priesthood has stores. We can offer a third way.\n(Option C is now available.)\n"
d3_l04_lith:  .asciiz "The Crystal Choir stands with you. Strike at the vampire's\nhunger itself, and we will not let the kingdom starve for\nit. (Option C is now available.)\n"

d3_choice_q:  .asciiz "\n>>> What is your ruling on the blood tax?\n"
d3_choice_a:  .asciiz "  A) Grant the tax. Order healthy miners to bleed.\n"
d3_choice_b:  .asciiz "  B) Refuse this round. Promise double next time.\n"
d3_choice_c:  .asciiz "  C) Abolish the tax. Vampires drink animal blood only.\n"

d3_after_a:   .asciiz "A king who keeps his word. Rare. The Guard remembers.\n"
d3_after_b:   .asciiz "Double, then. We will hold. But we will count the days,\nmy lord.\n"
d3_after_c:   .asciiz "... So this is what a crown looks like when it forgets\nwho built it.\n"

d3_n_a:       .asciiz "My lord, forgive me. The healthy ones are dying. The picks\nhave stopped. And Grimor - they found him in his bunk this\nmorning. Knife in his back. Nobody saw a thing. Nobody\never does.\n"

d3_n_b1:      .asciiz "A young soldier of mine. He could not wait. He took a\nservant in the west hall - too much, too fast. The body\nmust vanish before sunrise or I cannot promise what the\nothers will do. Help me bury this, or the gates open from\nthe inside.\n"
d3_n_b_q:     .asciiz "\n>>> Do you help Edmure cover up the murder?\n"
d3_n_b_qa:    .asciiz "  A) Help cover it up. Protect the realm.\n"
d3_n_b_qb:    .asciiz "  B) Refuse. Let the kingdom see what happened.\n"

d3_n_c1:      .asciiz "The torches above the gates go dark one by one. You step\nto your window. No vampires on the walls. They have walked\noff their post.\n"
d3_n_c2:      .asciiz "The gates are open, my king. What comes in is no longer\nmy concern.\n"
d3_n_c3:      .asciiz "A gap in the wall, my lord. A gap in the wall. The Order\nhas many sons who can hold a spear. Faithful ones. Devoted\nones. Say the word and the walls are manned again by dawn.\n"
d3_n_c_q:     .asciiz "\n>>> Accept Thomas's offer of priest-guards?\n"

d3_n_d:       .asciiz "Lithos walks with you tonight. The wind on the surface is\nsharp; the deep is warm. You spend the night among the\nLithari, in their cathedrals of song. Far above, Edmure\nslips into your empty chamber, finds you gone, and leaves\nin cold fury.\n"

# =============================================================================
# DAY 4 dialog strings - The Sacred Dig + Library
# =============================================================================
d4_l01: .asciiz "The Order has read the old scriptures again, my lord.\nThey want a new shaft. Deeper than any before. Down to the\nCrystal Mother herself. Father Thomas will press for the\nseal of the crown.\n"
d4_l02: .asciiz "Lithos is not a goddess. She is a power, sleeping. The\nDeliverance will not come on its own. We have miners. We\nhave shafts. We have your word - if you will give it.\nSign the dig, my king. End this.\n"
d4_l03: .asciiz "If your hands break the Mother, the deep breaks with her.\nThere is no Deliverance on the other side of that pick.\nThere is only silence, and after the silence, nothing.\n"
d4_l04_vamp: .asciiz "A word, my king. Alone. The priests have used you as a\npuppet since the day they cut your milk teeth. Sign this\nand the strings tighten until you cannot move. Do not give\nthem the dig. After that, there is no king left to undo it.\n"

d4_choice_q: .asciiz "\n>>> The Sacred Dig - do you authorize it?\n"
d4_choice_a: .asciiz "  A) Grant the dig.\n"
d4_choice_b: .asciiz "  B) Refuse the dig.\n"

d4_n01: .asciiz "You cannot sleep. The library is silent at this hour.\nBetween two shelves you find a book that should not be\nthere. It opens itself.\n"
d4_n02: .asciiz "You read of a 'Great Deliverance' - a shattered kingdom\nraised from the deep on faith alone. Beneath the title, in\nthe same hand: 'Author: Father Thomas.' Pages later:\nledgers. Names of miners. Numbers. The word 'expendable'\nwritten in his hand.\n"

d4_n_choice_q: .asciiz "\n>>> What do you do with the book?\n"
d4_n_choice_a: .asciiz "  A) Take it to your chamber. Study it. Some sacrifices\n     are worth the kingdom.\n"
d4_n_choice_b: .asciiz "  B) Burn the book. Have Father Thomas arrested before\n     dawn. (only if you chose B at the Turning Child)\n"

d4_n_after_a: .asciiz "If a hundred names are written down to save a hundred\nthousand... who am I to refuse the pen?\n"
d4_n_after_b: .asciiz "The fire takes the book quickly. Faster than guilt. By\ndawn Father Thomas is in irons. The Order has no voice in\ncourt tomorrow.\n"

d4_n_locked:  .asciiz "(You hesitate. This option is closed to a king who already\nhanded a child to the Order. The book stays open. Your hand\nreaches for it.)\n"

# =============================================================================
# DAY 5 / Endings
# =============================================================================
# Ending I - The Great Deliverance (default / book kept)
e1_l01: .asciiz "The fifth dawn. The new shaft is open. The Order leads the\nminers down, hymns rolling off the stone walls. You sit\nyour throne. You hear the singing stop. You hear something\nelse begin.\n"
e1_l02: .asciiz "At the bottom of the shaft they have built an altar around\nthe Crystal Mother. The miners are not workers today. They\nare kindling. The ledger you read was a guest list. Lithos\nscreams once, into every mind in the kingdom, and is silent.\n"
e1_l03: .asciiz "The kingdom rises now, my king. The realm shines. You have\ndone well. Sit. Stay seated. Smile when we tell you to.\nThe Order rules now. You... you are the smile on its face.\n"
e1_l04: .asciiz "\n*** ENDING I: THE GREAT DELIVERANCE ***\nYou saved nothing. You only signed it.\n"

# Day 5 Vampire branch (intro before C6)
e2_l01: .asciiz "The throne hall is colder than usual. Pale guards with red\neyes line the walls. Father Thomas is in the dungeon, so\nEdmure stands where the Advisor used to stand.\n"
e2_l02: .asciiz "The kingdom is safe, my king. The Order is silenced. The\nminers pay their tax without complaint. The deal is almost\ndone. One step left.\n"
e2_l03: .asciiz "The Fool King put us here to guard humanity. But humanity\nis weak, and sick, and short. You are not. You stood by\nus. You are not like the others. It is time the last thin\nline between us came down.\n"

e2_choice_q: .asciiz "\n>>> Edmure offers his blood. Do you drink?\n"
e2_choice_a: .asciiz "  A) Drink. Become a vampire. Rule forever.\n"
e2_choice_b: .asciiz "  B) Refuse. Remind Edmure who serves whom.\n"

# Ending II - The Eternal Night
e2a_l01: .asciiz "The torches in the throne hall go out one by one. Edmure\nkneels. He opens his own wrist. The blood is dark and\nthick. You drink.\n"
e2a_l02: .asciiz "The heartbeat speeds, then stops. In your mind, Lithos\nscreams - and is cut off. Cold strength fills your veins.\nYou do not need the torches anyway.\n"
e2a_l03: .asciiz "Years later. The throne is yours. Your skin is marble-pale,\nyour eyes burn red. Edmure stands at your right hand. The\nminers are no longer a people, they are herds, kept alive\nin deep farms only for their blood.\n"
e2a_l04: .asciiz "\n*** ENDING II: THE ETERNAL NIGHT ***\nYou saved the kingdom. You traded the word 'human' to do it.\n"

# Ending III - The Red Throne
e2b_l01: .asciiz "So that is your answer.\n"
e2b_l02: .asciiz "The doors of the throne hall lock from outside. Vampires\nstep out of every shadow. Edmure climbs the throne steps\nslowly.\n"
e2b_l03: .asciiz "The Fool King was clever. He gave us a place in his army\nbecause he could not stop us. He told us we were guardians.\nYou... you broke the Order for us. You weakened the miners\nfor us. You left no one who could stop us. And now you\nthink you can give orders?\n"
e2b_l04: .asciiz "Your hand finds your sword. A human reflex is slow for a\nvampire. Edmure is at your throat before the blade clears\nits sheath. You land on stone. Your blood pools, cold. The\nlast thing you see is Edmure sitting on your throne.\n"
e2b_l05: .asciiz "\n*** ENDING III: THE RED THRONE ***\nYou broke every chain that held the vampires back. They\nthanked you with your own throne.\n"

# Ending IV - The Crystal Heart
e4_l01: .asciiz "The throne hall is almost empty on the fifth day. The\nOrder has no voice. Edmure left the castle in fury the\nnight before, hunting a king who was not in his bed. Only\nValar and a handful of miners stand here.\n"
e4_l02: .asciiz "You silenced the dark, and you silenced the false light\ntoo. It is time, my king. The Mother heard your heart.\nShe is waiting.\n"
e4_l03: .asciiz "You leave the throne behind. Alone, you walk into tunnels\nno map has ever named. Pale violet and ice-blue light\ngrows around you the deeper you go. At the end of the\ndeep, the walls open into a cathedral of crystal.\n"
e4_l04: .asciiz "You trusted me. Against the dark ambitions and the bloody\nlies of men, you stood with me. You heard the quiet voice.\n"
e4_l05: .asciiz "You walk to her. You put your hands against the Mother.\nThe cold is gentle. The light fills you. There is no pain,\nonly belonging. Your skin turns slow and clear. Her mind\nopens, and yours steps inside.\n"
e4_l06: .asciiz "Years later. The miners who feared the Turn now welcome\nit - half of them have loved ones in the deep, and the\ndeep loves them back. The kingdom is not blood and it is\nnot faith. It is two crystal hearts beating side by side\nat its center.\n"
e4_l07: .asciiz "\n*** ENDING IV: THE CRYSTAL HEART ***\nNot a victory. A merger.\n"

